<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="270" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[813,1457,897,1054]" box="[813,903,897,923]" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[813,1457,897,1054]" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">
<bibRefCitation author="Dollfus" box="[813,979,929,956]" firstAuthor="Dollfus" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" pagination="1449 - 1452" refId="ref43497" refString="DOLLFUS R. P. 1974. - De l' Astropecten bonnieri R. Koehler, 1905 (Echinodermes, Stellerides). Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle de Paris (3) 254 (Zool. 176): 1449 - 1452. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 57256004" type="journal article" year="1974">Dollfus (1974)</bibRefCitation>
illustrates the 
<typeStatus box="[1146,1242,929,955]" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1905" box="[1283,1405,929,956]" class="Asteroidea" family="Astropectinidae" genus="Astropecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Paxillosida" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis box="[1283,1405,929,956]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">A. bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He corrects the type locality which is not ‘Red Sea’ as 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" pagination="64 - 470" refId="ref44333" refString="KOEHLER R. 1905 a. - Note preliminaire sur les echinodermes recueillis par l'expedition antarctique francaise du Dr Charcot (echinides, asterides et ophiures). Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle de Paris 11: 64 - 470. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 5034003" type="journal article" year="1905" yearSuffix="a">Koehler (1905a)</bibRefCitation>
wrote but rather the Persian Gulf (
<geoCoordinate box="[1258,1353,995,1022]" degrees="25" direction="north" minutes="10" orientation="latitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" precision="925" value="25.166666">25°10’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1362,1448,995,1022]" degrees="55" direction="east" minutes="10" orientation="longitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" precision="925" value="55.166668">55°10’E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[813,904,1027,1054]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.414016" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" unit="mi" value="15.0">15 miles</quantity>
off 
<collectingCountry box="[947,1017,1028,1054]" name="Oman" pageId="13" pageNumber="270">Oman</collectingCountry>
coast, 
<quantity box="[1092,1190,1028,1054]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="270" unit="m" value="23.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="18.0">18-29 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
